  stickyNoteInfos:
  - title: Spawning
    position:
      serializedVersion: 2
      x: 1294
      y: -1198
      width: 317
      height: 130
    contents: 'I decided to make the spawn rate for rain particles 1000 because trying
      lower values didn''t achieve the result I wanted of a rainstorm in the wide
      area of the VFX particle effect. I made sure that the scene wasn''t lagging
      as a result of all of the rain before committing to the high number. '
    theme: Classic
    textSize: Small
  - title: On Die
    position:
      serializedVersion: 2
      x: 2694
      y: 64
      width: 326
      height: 100
    contents: "When the particles \"die\" (reach the end of their lifetime), I made
      it so that a burst of droplets would trigger to emulate the effect of raindrops.
      \n"
    theme: Classic
    textSize: Small
  - title: Output Particle
    position:
      serializedVersion: 2
      x: 1392
      y: 414
      width: 190
      height: 100
    contents: Not much is changed here, as I enjoyed the base effect enough already.
      The size is kept at 0.1 in order to look like a normal sized raindrop.
    theme: Classic
    textSize: Small
  - title: InitializeParticle
    position:
      serializedVersion: 2
      x: 1377
      y: -663
      width: 223
      height: 271
    contents: 'Particles are being initialized in a wide area, enough to cover the
      entire area where the camera flies around in the cutscene. The lifetime is
      set to be a short 0.5 in order to compensate for the large amount of particles
      being spawned. Their colour is random between blue and a lighter shade of blue
      to give a bit of depth and variety to the rain. Lastly, their speed is set
      to 10 in order to simulate the speed at which real raindrops pour down, decently
      fast but slow enough to still be visible.

'
    theme: Classic
    textSize: Small
  - title: InitializeParticles
    position:
      serializedVersion: 2
      x: 2732
      y: 270
      width: 217
      height: 185
    contents: 'These particles spawn in a burst effect to give the impression of
      raindrops bursting. They have a lifetime of 1 so they have enough time to fall
      down, they take the colour and position of their source particle, and they
      have a random speed of descent between 0.5 and 2.5.  '
    theme: Classic
    textSize: Small
  - title: UpdateParticle
    position:
      serializedVersion: 2
      x: 2719
      y: 1350
      width: 209
      height: 116
    contents: These particles have Gravity and Linear Drag in order to make their
      burst and subsequent fall stand out from the slowly falling raindrops around
      them.
    theme: Classic
    textSize: Small
  - title: Output Particle
    position:
      serializedVersion: 2
      x: 2726
      y: 1767
      width: 182
      height: 100
    contents: 'The particles decrease in size and increase in transparency over their
      lifetime, in order to really sell the burst effect '
    theme: Classic
    textSize: Small
  - title: Rain Trail
    position:
      serializedVersion: 2
      x: 4390
      y: 13
      width: 254
      height: 100
    contents: 'This sequence is meant to give each raindrop a trail so they can be
      more visible falling through the sky. '
    theme: Classic
    textSize: Small
  - title: Initialize Particle Strip
    position:
      serializedVersion: 2
      x: 4370
      y: 378
      width: 198
      height: 100
    contents: 'Most values are taken from the source main particle in order to follow
      and mirror it properly, except for the size, as that''s been increased to 0.2
      to make the streams more visible. '
    theme: Classic
    textSize: Small
  - title: Output ParticleStrip
    position:
      serializedVersion: 2
      x: 3630
      y: 1184
      width: 179
      height: 175
    contents: 'Here, size gets larger over time for the trail, but the transparency
      also increases over time, creating a tail that is thinner at the end and thicker
      at the front closest to the particle. '
    theme: Classic
    textSize: Small
  categories: []
  uiBounds:
    serializedVersion: 2
    x: 1294
    y: -1294
    width: 3350
    height: 3455
